docs.abstract: A decade into the recovery, workers say they’re still dogged by the concessions they made when the economy was weak.
docs.snippet: A decade into the recovery, workers say they’re still dogged by the concessions they made when the economy was weak.
docs.lead_paragraph: At first glance, it may seem like a paradox: Even as the economy rides a 10-year winning streak, tens of thousands of workers across the country, from General Motors employees to teachers in Chicago, are striking to win better wages and benefits.

headline.main: In a Strong Economy, Why Are So Many Workers on Strike?
headline.print_headline: Workers Chase Spoils of Boom On Picket Lines

docs.abstract: After reports of progress between the automaker and the striking United Auto Workers, the company’s plants in Mexico are reportedly a sticking point.
docs.snippet: After reports of progress between the automaker and the striking United Auto Workers, the company’s plants in Mexico are reportedly a sticking point.
docs.lead_paragraph: General Motors and the striking United Auto Workers hit a roadblock in contract talks on Sunday over the question of moving production from Mexico to plants in the United States, two people close to the talks said.

headline.main: Talks to End G.M. Strike Take ‘Turn for the Worse,’ U.A.W. Says
headline.print_headline: Union Says G.M. Talks Take ‘Turn for the Worse’

docs.abstract: The union said a company offer fell short on wages, health care and other issues. But developments suggested that talks might be in their final phase.
docs.snippet: The union said a company offer fell short on wages, health care and other issues. But developments suggested that talks might be in their final phase.
docs.lead_paragraph: The United Auto Workers reported Tuesday that it had exchanged contract proposals with General Motors, but said many issues remained unresolved in talks that would end the strike that has shut down 34 factories in the United States for more than two weeks.

headline.main: U.A.W. Exchanges Proposals With G.M. but Says a Gulf Remains
headline.print_headline: U.A.W. Swaps Offers With G.M., but Says Gulf Remains
